"review_level": "None",
"content": "<h2>Dead bodies were to be treated with respect</h2>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Sam21:12-2Sam21:14\">2SA 21:12–21:14</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eccl6:3\">ECC 6:3</a></p>\n<h2>Unburied dead bodies were a sign of God's curse upon Israel</h2>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut28:26\">DEU 28:26</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer16:4\">JER 16:4</a></p>\n<h2>Contact with dead bodies</h2>\n<h3>The high priest was not to touch a dead body</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev21:11\">LEV 21:11</a></p>\n<h3>Contact with a dead body made a person unclean</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num19:11\">NUM 19:11</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num9:6-Num9:10\">NUM 9:6–9:10</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num19:16\">NUM 19:16</a></p>\n<h3>Jesus Christ was willing to touch a dead body</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt9:25\">MAT 9:25</a> parallels <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark5:41\">MRK 5:41</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke8:54\">LUK 8:54</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark9:26-Mark9:27\">MRK 9:26–9:27</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke7:14\">LUK 7:14</a></p>\n<h3>The reluctance to approach dead bodies because of the smell</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/John11:39\">JHN 11:39</a></p>",
